<ab><lb n="1"/>  <w lemma="ὁ"><supplied reason="lost">τ</supplied>ὴν</w>  <persName type="divine"><name>Ὑγήαν</name></persName>  <persName type="emperor"><name nymRef="#Καῖσαρ">Καίσα<supplied reason="lost">ρι</supplied></name>  <name nymRef="#Σεβαστός"><supplied reason="lost">Σεβ</supplied><lb n="2" break="no"/><supplied reason="lost">α</supplied>στ<unclear reason="damage">ῶ</unclear>ι</name></persName> <w lemma="καί">καὶ</w> <w lemma="ὁ">τῶι</w> <w lemma="δῆμος">δή<unclear reason="damage">μ</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ωι</supplied></w>  <lb n="3"/><persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Μολοσσός"><supplied reason="lost">Μ</supplied>ολοσσὸς</name>  <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Χρυσάορος">Χρυσ<unclear reason="damage">ά</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ο</supplied><lb n="4" break="no"/><supplied reason="lost">ρ</supplied>ος</name></persName></persName> <w lemma="ὁ">ὁ</w> <w lemma="ἱερεύς">ἱερεὺς</w> <w lemma="ὁ">τῆς</w> <persName type="divine"><name>Ὑγ<supplied reason="lost">ήας</supplied></name></persName></ab>
</div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>The <supplied reason="subaudible">statue of</supplied> Hygeia <supplied reason="explanation">Health</supplied> for Caesar Augustus and the People: Molossos son of Chrysaor, the priest of Hygeia <supplied reason="subaudible">set it up</supplied>.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>See Reynolds. loc.cit., with 'Further information', 109, and 'Ruler-cult', 43</p>
